# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Rust / Cargo
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Build output. Cargo writes all compiled binaries, intermediate object
# files, incremental compilation caches, and dependency builds here.
# It's huge, machine-specific, and fully reproducible from source — never commit it.
target/

# Cargo.lock: KEEP committed for binaries/applications (this repo) so builds
# are reproducible. IGNORE it only for libraries published to crates.io,
# so downstream users resolve their own dependency versions.
# (Not ignored here — these are binary crates.)

# Backup files Cargo or rustfmt may leave behind
**/*.rs.bk

# Perf profiling output (cargo flamegraph, etc.)
*.perf
perf.data*
flamegraph.svg

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Editor / IDE
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# rust-analyzer / IntelliJ scratch state
.idea/
*.iml

# VS Code: usually personal — uncomment to ignore. Some teams commit
# .vscode/settings.json with shared formatter/lint settings.
# .vscode/

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OS junk
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Secrets / local env
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
*.pem
